sql:
SELECT review_id, asin, review_date
FROM reviews
ORDER BY review_date DESC;

SELECT review_date
FROM reviews
ORDER BY review_date DESC;

SELECT AVG(overall) AS average_rating
FROM reviews
WHERE reviewer_id = 12345;

external_knowledge:
- Top-level categories are those without a parent category, indicating the highest level in the hierarchy;
- Compound sentiment scores are a measure of the overall sentiment (positive or negative) in a review;
- Usefulness scores are ratings by other users indicating how helpful a review is.
